# Infrastructure as Code Standards

## Resource Organization
- Group related resources into logical constructs
- Use proper resource naming conventions
- Implement proper resource tagging
- Follow the principle of least privilege
- Use proper resource dependencies

## Security Best Practices
- Use service accounts with minimal permissions
- Implement proper IAM roles and policies
- Use secrets management for sensitive data
- Implement proper network security
- Use proper encryption for data at rest and in transit

## Resource Management
- Use proper resource lifecycle management
- Implement proper backup and recovery
- Use proper resource scaling
- Implement proper monitoring and logging
- Use proper resource cleanup

## Infrastructure Patterns
- Use proper resource reuse
- Implement proper resource abstraction
- Use proper resource composition
- Implement proper resource validation
- Use proper resource testing

## Deployment
- Use proper deployment strategies
- Implement proper rollback procedures
- Use proper deployment validation
- Implement proper deployment monitoring
- Use proper deployment documentation

## Cost Management
- Use proper resource sizing
- Implement proper cost monitoring
- Use proper cost optimization
- Implement proper cost reporting
- Use proper cost documentation


